71.1	Heart_disease	Cardiovascular disease	Cardiovascular disease or heart disease is a class of diseases that involve the heart or blood vessels . While the term technically refers to any disease that affects the cardiovascular system (as used in MeSH C14 or International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems 10th Revision (ICD10), ICD-10 Chapter IX: Diseases of the circulatory system), it is often used to refer to those related to atherosclerosis and/or hypertension. The causes, mechanisms, and treatments of these conditions often overlap.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Cardiac_amyloidosis_very_high_mag_movat.jpg/230px-Cardiac_amyloidosis_very_high_mag_movat.jpg
